Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy for Blueprint Mobile App
Last updated: 27 Dec 2023
This Privacy Policy governs how Blueprint Mobile App ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, maintains, and discloses information from users ("User" or "you") of the Blueprint mobile application ("App") and [https://heyblueprint.app] ("Website").
Information Collection and Use
1.1 Personal Information
We collect personal information from Users in various ways, including visits to our Website, registration on the App, orders, newsletter subscriptions, forms, and interactions with App features. This includes your name, email address, phone number, and billing information, provided voluntarily by Users.
1.2 Non-Personal Information
We collect non-personal information during User interactions with our App or Website, such as device type, operating system, and browser name.
Information Usage
2.1 Personal Information
We use personal information to personalize User experience, improve our App, and communicate via email.
2.2 Non-Personal Information
We use non-personal information to analyze trends, administer the App, and improve user experience.
Data Protection
We implement data collection, storage, and processing practices, and security measures to protect personal information.
Sharing Personal Information
We do not sell personal information. We may share aggregated demographic information with partners.
Third-Party Websites and Services
We are not responsible for the content or practices of third-party websites linked to our App or Website.
Compliance with Legal Obligations
We may disclose personal information if required by law.
Blueprint Mobile App use and transfer to any other app of information received from Google APIs will adhere to
Google API Services User Data Policy
, including the Limited Use requirements.
User Consent for Data Use
We obtain explicit consent from users before accessing Google user data.
Security Measures for Google Data
We implement robust security measures, including encrypted data transmission using SSL/TLS, regular security audits, and strict access controls, to protect Google user data.
Data Retention and Deletion Policy
User data is retained in Blueprint servers if user chooses to enable data backup and can be deleted upon user request, complying with data protection regulations.
Your Privacy Controls
At Blueprint Mobile App, you retain full rights to your data. We collect information to provide and improve our services, communicate with you, and ensure the safety of our services. We will never sell your personal data to third parties and only share data with your permission or when legally required. Our services use GDPR-compliant third-party services when necessary, with strong security measures to protect your data.
Cookies and Data Usage
We use cookies on our Website to optimize user experience. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but this may affect the functionality of our services. All data transmitted through our service is secured with SSL protocol.
Data Retention and Security
We employ strong security features to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Information is retained until you delete your account, with a 90-day retention in backup archives post-deletion. Subscription and transaction records are kept longer as per legal requirements.
Data Deletion
You can request to delete your account and associated data through our App settings. Upon account deletion, we will cease providing services to you and remove your personal information as per your request.
Changes to This Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy. Any changes will be indicated by an updated revision date. Significant changes will be communicated more prominently. Continued use of our App or Website after such changes constitutes acceptance of the new policy.
Contact Us
For questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us via hello@getdisciplined.app
This Privacy Policy is effective as of 16 December 2023.